<h2><b>What is a Gram?</b></h2>
<p>A gram is a term used in cooking or measuring to signify 1/1000th of a k=
ilogram in the international system of units or metric system.</p>
<h2><b>What is an Ounce?</b></h2>
<p>An ounce measures liquids or solids equivalent to 1/16th of a pound or 2=
8.35 grams in the United States. In the U.S. Customary System, a liquid oun=
ce equals 29.57 milliliters of liquid.</p>
<p>The ounce is part of the U.S. Customary System and the British Imperial =
Measurement System. The ounce is smaller in the British Imperial system, eq=
uivalent to 1/20th of a pint or 28.41 milliliters. It is also part of the a=
pothecaries=E2=80=99 system of measurement used in the British Isles; howev=
er, an apothecary ounce is slightly bigger, equivalent to 31.103 grams.</p>
<h2><b>How Many Grams in an Ounce?</b></h2>
<div class=3D"conversion-calculator">
<h3 class=3D"title-calculator">Grams(g) to Ounces Conversion</h3>
<p>Type a value in the Grams(g) field to convert the value to Ounces:</p>
<p>
    <label>Grams(g)</label><br>
    <input id=3D"inputGrams" type=3D"number" placeholder=3D"Grams">
  </p>
<div class=3D"calculator-result">
<p>Ounces: <span id=3D"outputOunces">=E2=80=93</span></p>
</div>
<p> =20
</p></div>
<p>There are approximately 28.35 grams in an ounce. Multiply the number of =
ounces you need by 28.35 to determine the equivalent amount of grams. If yo=
u=E2=80=99re going from grams to ounces, the simplest way to convert is to =
divide by 28.35.</p>
<p>To convert ounces to grams, you need to multiply by 28.35.</p>
<p><code>Grams =3D ounces X 28.35.</code></p>
<p>To convert grams to ounces, divide by 28.35.</p>
