<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>What is the metric equivalent grams to 1 oz?</h3>
<p>There are 28.35 grams in an ounce. For cooking recipes, ounce-to-gram co=
nversions are rounded down to 28 grams per ounce.</p>
<h3>Is 100g equal to 4 oz?</h3>
<p>One hundred grams is equivalent to 3.5 ounces. For best results, use exa=
ct ounce measurements for recipes.</p>
<h3>Is one ounce of liquid the same as one ounce of solid?</h3>
<p>The measurement of an ounce changes when you are measuring a solid versu=
s measuring a liquid. One ounce of a solid equals 28.35 grams, while one ou=
nce of liquid equals 29.57 milliliters.</p>
<h3>How to measure grams and ounces?</h3>
<p>The best way to measure grams is using a kitchen scale. The best way to =
measure ounces is by using a measuring cup with ounce lines.</p>
